    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1Manager" kindref="compound">Manager</ref> that processes damage commands and updates entity health. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1HealthManager" kindref="compound">HealthManager</ref> implements the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1Manager" kindref="compound">Manager</ref> interface for integration into the game loop flush cycle, and the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1messaging_1_1command_1_1TypedCommandHandler" kindref="compound">TypedCommandHandler</ref> interface for <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1damage_1_1commands_1_1ApplyDamageCommand" kindref="compound">ApplyDamageCommand</ref> so that incoming damage is queued and applied in batch.</para>
<para>During <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1HealthManager_1a09a3a9b1c6903875df52dfacc0279dea" kindref="member">flush()</ref>, each queued <ref refid="structhelios_1_1engine_1_1common_1_1types_1_1DamageContext" kindref="compound">DamageContext</ref> is resolved: the target&apos;s <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1components_1_1HealthComponent" kindref="compound">HealthComponent</ref> is damaged, a <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1events_1_1HealthChangedEvent" kindref="compound">HealthChangedEvent</ref> is emitted, and if health reaches zero a <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1events_1_1HealthDepletedEvent" kindref="compound">HealthDepletedEvent</ref> is pushed together with an optional <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1lifecycle_1_1components_1_1DeadTagComponent" kindref="compound">DeadTagComponent</ref>.</para>
<para>Event phases:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1events_1_1HealthChangedEvent" kindref="compound">HealthChangedEvent</ref> is pushed to the **phase** bus (available to systems in the next phase).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1events_1_1HealthDepletedEvent" kindref="compound">HealthDepletedEvent</ref> is pushed to the **pass** bus (available to systems after commit within the same pass).</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1damage_1_1commands_1_1ApplyDamageCommand" kindref="compound">ApplyDamageCommand</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1components_1_1HealthComponent" kindref="compound">HealthComponent</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1health_1_1events_1_1HealthDepletedEvent" kindref="compound">HealthDepletedEvent</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1Manager" kindref="compound">Manager</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
